author: Zachary Cohen and Marshall Cohen, CNN
title: Trump retweets Russian propaganda about Biden that US intel agencies say is intended to influence 2020 election
description: President Donald Trump on Sunday night retweeted Russian propaganda about former Vice President Joe Biden that the US intelligence community recently announced was part of Moscow's ongoing effort to "denigrate" the Democrat ahead of November's election.
source.name: CNN

author: Parija Bhatnagar, CNN Business
title: Remember Payless? Shoe seller is back and opening its first US store in November
description: After filing for bankruptcy protection for the second time and shutting all of its 2,100 stores in the US last year, discount shoe chain Payless is attempting a comeback.
source.name: CNN

author: Alaa Elassar, CNN
title: Church is enforcing social distancing with humorous signs referencing scripture
description: A church pastor dedicated to bringing joy amid difficult times is using humor to help social distance his congregation during Sunday services.
source.name: CNN

author: Holmes Lybrand and Tara Subramaniam, CNN
title: Fact check: Is Harris the most liberal member of Senate?
description: After former Vice President Joe Biden announced California Sen. Kamala Harris as his running mate, critics were quick to label her as far left while some progressives bemoaned her as too much of a moderate.

author: Erica Orden and Katelyn Polantz, CNN
title: Appeals court lets emoluments case against Trump continue
description: An ethics lawsuit against President Donald Trump that argues his business interests are conflicts of interest and violate the US Constitution can continue in federal court, a federal appeals court said Monday.
source.name: CNN
